So I've had another look at this and remain stuck at the same point. I'll try again tomorrow (well today as it's past midnight) and ask around on IRC, but I doubt I'll get any progress. The problem I'm facing is the following:

In `SassSrcNode` the property [`path`](https://github.com/jrief/django-sass-processor/blob/master/sass_processor/templatetags/sass_tags.py#L28-L30) is defined to use in `compilescss.py`'s [`parse_template`](https://github.com/jrief/django-sass-processor/blob/master/sass_processor/management/commands/compilescss.py#L265). The problem is that, as far as I understand, Jinja2 does not allow an extension to immediately parse a variable:

```jinja2
{% set source = 'tests/css/main.scss' %}
{% sass_src source %}
{# 'tests/css/main.scss' cannot be immediately retrieved from `source`. #}
```

Therefore I cannot make sure that the node the extension returns has the property `path` set so it can be used in `parse_template`. So it complains that the `path` property is not set when a variable is used in one of the templates.

