Hey everyone!  Great work so far.

I can see everyone's sides to this issue, but my style errs more towards that of @rueberger.  

That being said, I do think that it's likely possible to use metaclasses in a way similar to Django, Luigi, etc. to wrap some OO around what already exists.  A simple example would be:

```
from sacred import Experiment

ex = Experiment('test')

class SimpleExperiment(object):
    three = 3

    @staticmethod
    @ex.config
    def cfg():
        one = 1
        two =2

    @staticmethod
    @ex.automain
    def run(one, two):
        return one + two + SimpleExperiment.three
```

I'm going to run with this a bit more in the coming days, but I wanted to see if anyone had any thoughts or has already went down this route, only to find something I'm missing?

