It looks like there is a problem with the logging code in `examples/platforms/nrf52840/logging.c` starting on 168:

    length += vsnprintf(&logString[length], (LOG_PARSE_BUFFER_SIZE - length),
                        aFormat, paramList);
    logString[length++] = '\n';
    va_end(paramList);

This code is making an incorrect assumption about the return value of `vsnprintf()`. The return value of the `printf()` functions is **NOT** the number of bytes written to the string, it is the number of characters that it would have output if there were no length constraints. For example, both of the following calls to `snprintf()` will return the value 10:

* `snprintf(mystring, 5, "0123456789");`
* `snprintf(mystring, 20, "0123456789");`

By changing the code in question to the following, the problem is addressed:

    length += vsnprintf(&logString[length], (LOG_PARSE_BUFFER_SIZE - length),
                        aFormat, paramList);
    if (length > LOG_PARSE_BUFFER_SIZE)
    {
        length = LOG_PARSE_BUFFER_SIZE;
    }
    logString[length++] = '\n';
    va_end(paramList);

